         <abstract>
            <p>We derive a posteriori bounds for (V - |hat V) and its difference quotient &lt;tex-math&gt;$(V - \hat V)_x$&lt;/tex-math&gt;, where V and |hat V are, respectively, the exact and computed solution of a difference approximation to a mildly nonlinear parabolic initial boundary problem, with a known steady-state solution. It is assumed that the computation is over a long interval of time. The estimates are valid for a class of difference approximations, which includes the Crank-Nicolson method, and are of the same magnitude for both &lt;tex-math&gt;$(V - \hat V)$&lt;/tex-math&gt; and &lt;tex-math&gt;$(V - \hat V)_x$&lt;/tex-math&gt;.</p>
          </abstract>
